{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17658534","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17658534"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:49:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:49:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20768"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20768","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20768"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13643"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95759"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13643"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20768"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78560"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"11582"},{"type":"tags","id":"11749"},{"type":"tags","id":"12622"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"32808"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32810"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95759","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/95759"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECellular aging is influenced by various molecular pathways that respond to environmental factors. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the molecular mechanisms by which caloric restriction increases longevity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increased IGF-1 signaling and decreased sirtuin activity","Decreased NAD+ availability and increased cellular metabolism","Increased mTOR activation and decreased DNA repair","Decreased IGF-1 signaling and increased sirtuin activity","Increased apoptosis and decreased protein folding"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECaloric restriction increases longevity through \u003Cstrong\u003Edecreased IGF-1 signaling and increased sirtuin activity\u003C/strong\u003E. When caloric intake is reduced, the insulin and insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF-1) pathway is attenuated, which leads to lower rates of cell growth, metabolism, and potentially reduced cellular damage. Simultaneously, caloric restriction increases the activity of sirtuins, particularly sirtuin-6, which promotes genomic integrity by activating DNA repair enzymes through deacylation and contributes to metabolic adaptations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased IGF-1 signaling and decreased sirtuin activity\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the opposite of what occurs during caloric restriction. Increased IGF-1 signaling promotes an anabolic state with cell growth and replication, while decreased sirtuin activity would reduce longevity-promoting effects.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased mTOR activation and decreased DNA repair\u003C/strong\u003E - mTOR (mammalian target of rapamycin) is downstream of IGF-1 and is actually inhibited during caloric restriction, not activated. DNA repair is enhanced, not decreased, primarily through sirtuin activity.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased NAD+ availability and increased cellular metabolism\u003C/strong\u003E - Sirtuins are NAD+-dependent deacetylases, and their activity requires NAD+ availability. Caloric restriction typically decreases cellular metabolism rather than increasing it.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased apoptosis and decreased protein folding\u003C/strong\u003E - Sirtuins actually reduce apoptosis and stimulate protein folding, both of which contribute to increased longevity.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe effects of caloric restriction can be partially mimicked by rapamycin, which inhibits mTOR. While compounds like those found in red wine have been suggested to activate sirtuins, more research is needed before sirtuin-activating interventions can be reliably used to increase human longevity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Caloric restriction increases life span in all eukaryotic species tested, including promising results in nonhuman primates.","The insulin/IGF-1 signaling pathway and sirtuins are two major neurohormonal circuits that regulate metabolism and influence aging.","Caloric restriction increases longevity by attenuating IGF-1 signaling and increasing sirtuin activity, particularly sirtuin-6."],"references":["Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC. Robbins and Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease. 10th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2020. Chapter 2; page 68-69."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78560"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20768"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78560","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78560"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-29T12:36:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-29T12:37:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13643"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95759"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11582","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11582"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Cell injury, cell death and adaptations","synonyms":[],"description"